4/11/00
  Modified monitor.c so that it will not print status if video stops.
  Instead it will turn LED on/off every 15 sec.

  Modified pbmsg.h and splicer.c: re-type timeout from Int32 to Unit32
  to match with the definition defined in PPC.

  Version 1 in clearCase:
      dpi.000411, dpi206.fls, dpi Ver 19.1, common Ver 2.1


4/13/00
  Removed old rate conversion code in rateconv.c.


4/14/00
  Test of HITS bypass without splicing and rate conversion: Video stopped
      after about 6 hours.  Seems there are some syntax error in the bitstream
      that PES header and picture_coding_extension is missing.
  Suspect this is due to a undetected stack overflow.  Modify checkTask() to
      check more words on the stack to detect overflow problem.

  There are more than 1 task that modify muxBacklog and rcBacklog.
  Use interrupt protected increment and decrement.
  This will avoid some mistakes in the log file.

  Add a new compilation flag ERR_HDL for error handling flag (allows error
  in syntax).
  Note: we shall indicate to mux that whether a picture has syntax error or not.
        A picture with syntax error should not be rate converted.


